# Podcast workflow

This repo prepares **RSS.com drafts only**. Never publish live episodes via the API.

## New episode

When the user says "new episode", "prepare episode", or "start episode about …", use the **new-episode** skill (`.cursor/skills/new-episode/SKILL.md`).

## File preferences

- Prefer editing **markdown** (`script.md`, `description.md`) over YAML unless metadata is needed
- `script.md` is for planning only — not sent to RSS.com
- `description.md` is what gets uploaded as the episode description

## Before publish

Confirm all of the following:

1. MP3 exists (in episode folder or `RSSCOM_AUDIO_DIR`)
2. `description.md` is non-empty
3. `make dry-run EPISODE=...` succeeded

Run dry-run before every publish. Offer to run it in the terminal for the user.

## Publish

Use `make publish EPISODE=episodes/...` — never call the RSS.com API to publish live.

After publish, print the dashboard URL from the terminal output.

## Secrets

Never commit `.env`. Never ask the user to paste API keys into chat — they belong in `.env` only.
